2. Extract result.amount from the response
3. Use result.amount as this expectedAmount parameter

EXAMPLE:
const calc = await calculateSellAmount({ tokenName: 'woohoo', amount: '10', type: 'native' });
// calc.amount = "16843.7579794843252"
await sell({ tokenName: 'woohoo', amount: '10', type: 'native', expectedAmount: calc.amount, ... });
// Use calc.amount ("16843.7579794843252"), NOT the input '10'

updateMessage.description:
Update a message's content.

Updates the content of an existing message (CHAT or COMMENT).
Only the original author can update their message.
The message will have an updatedAt timestamp after editing.

RETURNS: {
  message: {
    id, type, tokenName, tokenImage, userAddress, userProfile,
    content, createdAt, updatedAt, deletedAt, flagCount, reactions
  }
}

Authentication: Requires JWT session (call gala_launchpad_login first)
Authorization: Message author only.

getPinnedMessage.description:
Get the currently pinned message for a token.

Retrieves the pinned message details including content, sender, and when it was pinned.
Returns null if no message is currently pinned.

RETURNS: {
  message: {
    id, tokenName, content, userAddress, userProfile,
    createdAt, pinnedAt, pinnedBy
  } | null
}

Authentication: None required (public endpoint)

getRestrictedNames.description:
Get the restricted token names content.

Returns newline-separated words that cannot be used in token names.
Contains offensive words - API response not publicly exposed.

**Authorization:** Overseer only (JWT)

RETURNS: {
  success: true,
  data: { content: "scam\nrug\nfake\n..." }
}

getTrades.description:
Query trades with flexible filtering options.

Returns paginated list of trades with metadata using cursor-based pagination.
At least one of tokenName or userAddress is required.

Filters:
- tokenName: Filter by token name (e.g., 'anime')
- userAddress: Filter by user wallet address
- txnType: Filter by trade direction ('BUY' or 'SELL')
- startDate/endDate: Filter by date range (ISO 8601)
- minAmount/maxAmount: Filter by trade amount range

RETURNS: { trades: [{ txnId, txnType, inputAmount, outputAmount, userAddress, tokenName, tokenImage, createdAt }], pageInfo: { hasNextPage, endCursor, hasPreviousPage, startCursor } }

Examples:
- Get all trades for a token: { tokenName: 'anime' }
- Get all trades by a user: { userAddress: 'eth|123...' }
- Get only buy trades: { tokenName: 'anime', txnType: 'BUY' }
- Get trades in date range: { tokenName: 'anime', startDate: '2024-01-01', endDate: '2024-12-31' }
- Get large trades: { tokenName: 'anime', minAmount: 1000 }

Public endpoint - no authentication required.
